besides, it's no like you're doing these things just for the flags.  decide what kind of guild you're in...if it's a big uber pwnd-VT-for-months kind of guild then you can walk through any of those flag fights any time you want to with zero effort.  it it's a smaller guild moving into pop out of velious/lower luclin then those flag mobs will be dropping nice loot that your people will want, so people should be begging to go do those fights more often.<br>
<br>
really, i think out of all of it, the poj trials are the simplest.  it's not a raid, it doesn't take 7 hours...it's 6 people for maybe 45 mins if you do it right.  the planes are the homes of gods, within them are stronger mobs than anything else in the game...pop is the new endgame, it's not meant to be like kunark or luclin, having all types of mobs for all levels.  it's the idea of velious taken 10x farther.  i mean, i'd like to walk into Vex Thal right now...but i'm looking at about 40 hours of shard camping and an (i hope) emp kill.  it it hard? yea.  is it worth it?  that depends on who you ask.  should it be made easier just because some people can't do it?  no.<br>
<br>
